    {
      "id": "PopularPost369531",
      "post_content": "This was always the drop that followed [Sengir Vampire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sengir Vampire) in *Alpha* mono-black decks. The variable power and toughness made it black's win condition next to [Drain Life](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Drain Life), and it was a feared card for a long time.  \n  \nWhat has always puzzled me is its somewhat arbitrary mana cost. Personally I would have been fine if it cost ![4](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=4&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol) or even ![3](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=3&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol)![Black](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=B&type=symbol), since it gets the most benefit out of decks running lots of swamps anyway. Using [Sol Ring](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sol Ring) or [Mana Vault](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mana Vault) to power it out would just leave it undersized for its price. Why make such an monocolor card so easy to splash?",
      "posted_by": "Equinox523",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost369531\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_post\">This was always the drop that followed <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sengir Vampire\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sengir Vampire\">Sengir Vampire</a> in <i>Alpha</i> mono-black decks.  The variable power and toughness made it black's win condition next to <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Drain Life\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Drain Life\">Drain Life</a>, and it was a feared card for a long time.<br/><br/>What has always puzzled me is its somewhat arbitrary mana cost.  Personally I would have been fine if it cost <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"4\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=4&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/> or even <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"3\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=3&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Black\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=B&amp;type=symbol\"/>, since it gets the most benefit out of decks running lots of swamps anyway.  Using <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sol Ring\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sol Ring\">Sol Ring</a> or <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mana Vault\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mana Vault\">Mana Vault</a> to power it out would just leave it undersized for its price.  Why make such an monocolor card so easy to splash?</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '369531'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\r\n                                Posted By: \r\n                                <span id=\"PostedBy1136\">Equinox523</span>\r\n                                (4/2/2014 2:08:47 PM)\r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    Rating:\u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n<div class=\"starRating\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl07_postRating_starRating\"><img alt=\"0.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"1.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"2.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"3.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"4.5\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/LeftClearSmall.png\"/><img alt=\"5.0\" src=\"../../Images/Stars/RightClearSmall.png\"/>\n<br/>\n</div>\n</div>\n<br class=\"clear\"/>\n</div>\n<div class=\"postRating\">\n<div class=\"postRatingLabel\">\r\n                                    \u00a0\r\n                                </div>\n<div style=\"float: left;\">\n</